HEADWORD: Tiresome
<hw>Tire"some</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Fitted or tending to
tire; exhausted; wearisome; fatiguing; tedious; <as>as, a
<ex>tiresome</ex> journey; a <ex>tiresome</ex> discourse.</as></def> --
<wordforms><wf>Tire"some*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Tire"some*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

